 016:     return the approximate distance between 2 time series with O(N)
 017:         time and memory complexity
 018:         Parameters
 019:         ----------
 020:         x : array_like
 021:             input array 1
 022:         y : array_like
 023:             input array 2
 024:         radius : int
 025:             size of neighborhood when expanding the path. A higher value will
 026:             increase the accuracy of the calculation but also increase time
 027:             and memory consumption. A radius equal to the size of x and y will
 028:             yield an exact dynamic time warping calculation.
 029:         dist : function or int
 030:             The method for calculating the distance between x[i] and y[j]. If
 031:             dist is an int of value p > 0, then the p-norm will be used. If
 032:             dist is a function then dist(x[i], y[j]) will be used. If dist is
 033:             None then abs(x[i] - y[j]) will be used.
 034:         Returns
 035:         -------
